==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Toady
<hw>Toad"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Toadies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Shortened from
<ets>toadeater</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A mean flatterer; a
toadeater; a sycophant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Before I had been standing at the window five minutes, they
somehow conveyed to me that they were all <qex>toadies</qex> and
humbugs.</q> <rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A coarse, rustic woman.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1514 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toady</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Toady
<hw>Toad"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
